And we can go ahead and hit this commit button.

00:45:14.159 --> 00:45:15.360
We'll get this pop-up menu.

00:45:16.000 --> 00:45:17.120
Both files are brand new,

00:45:17.120 --> 00:45:18.479
which is why everything is green.

00:45:19.679 --> 00:45:21.360
And let's go ahead and give it a commit message.

00:45:21.360 --> 00:45:23.199
Again, try to be informative here.

00:45:23.840 --> 00:45:25.520
Create Shiny app.

00:45:26.320 --> 00:45:27.040
And we'll hit commit.

00:45:28.639 --> 00:45:29.840
I'll close out of this.

00:45:29.840 --> 00:45:31.679
We'll get that same information window,

00:45:31.679 --> 00:45:34.800
letting us know that we're one commit ahead locally

00:45:34.800 --> 00:45:36.080
than with the GitHub.

00:45:36.080 --> 00:45:38.159
So let's go ahead and push those changes to GitHub.

00:45:40.560 --> 00:45:41.439
And that's it.

00:45:41.439 --> 00:45:43.199
We'll come back to my GitHub repository.

00:45:43.199 --> 00:45:44.239
I'll refresh my page.

00:45:45.679 --> 00:45:47.040
