And then the very first option is import from Git.

00:46:16.080 --> 00:46:17.520
So I'm going to select this option.

00:46:18.159 --> 00:46:19.439
And the first thing we need to provide

00:46:19.439 --> 00:46:21.040
is that GitHub repository.

00:46:21.040 --> 00:46:23.600
So let me come back here, come back to this code,

00:46:24.320 --> 00:46:28.000
copy my repository URL, and then paste it right here.

00:46:29.840 --> 00:46:30.560
I'll hit next.

00:46:31.120 --> 00:46:32.320
And what it's going to do right now

00:46:32.320 --> 00:46:35.520
is to ask you what branch do you want to publish from?

00:46:35.520 --> 00:46:37.760
And this is another really cool workflow

00:46:37.760 --> 00:46:40.800
because you can actually publish the same piece of content

00:46:40.800 --> 00:46:42.560
but multiple versions of it

00:46:42.560 --> 00:46:44.479
depending on what branch you want to deploy from.

00:46:45.040 --> 00:46:46.239
So we can select main

00:46:46.239 --> 00:46:48.159
or we can select that new branch that we created.

00:46:48.719 --> 00:46:50.320
So we're going to select test branch one

00:46:50.320 --> 00:46:52.560
because that's where everything is currently residing.

00:46:52.560 --> 00:46:53.280
We'll hit next.

00:46:54.159 --> 00:46:56.239
It's going to look for deployable directories.

00:46:56.800 --> 00:46:59.199
Really, it's searching for this manifest file.

00:46:59.199 --> 00:47:00.560
And if it finds it, it's going to say,

00:47:00.560 --> 00:47:02.399
OK, I have the information needed

00:47:02.399 --> 00:47:04.320
to publish the content in this directory.

00:47:05.120 --> 00:47:06.800
So it's in this directory.

00:47:06.800 --> 00:47:08.239
And all we have to do is give it a title.

00:47:08.239 --> 00:47:10.479
So I'll call it NHS Shiny.

00:47:10.479 --> 00:47:11.840
And we'll deploy the content.

00:47:12.560 --> 00:47:14.639
And so what's happening right now is

00:47:14.639 --> 00:47:16.800
Connect is reading that manifest file

00:47:16.800 --> 00:47:18.639
and it's replicating my environment.

00:47:18.639 --> 00:47:21.760
So what our version packages, all those versions,

00:47:21.760 --> 00:47:22.800
once that's prepared,

00:47:22.800 --> 00:47:25.600
it'll then deploy that Shiny application

00:47:25.600 --> 00:47:27.120
directly to Posit Connect.

00:47:29.520 --> 00:47:32.000
All right, so we'll just give this a few seconds to boot up.

00:47:32.000 --> 00:47:34.560
But as a publisher, so I'm the publisher,

00:47:34.560 --> 00:47:36.159
the owner of this piece of content,

00:47:36.159 --> 00:47:38.719
I have some additional controls right here in the top,

00:47:38.719 --> 00:47:39.679
this gear icon.

00:47:40.479 --> 00:47:42.800
And most importantly, I have access controls.

00:47:42.800 --> 00:47:45.840
All right, so here's that Shiny application that we created.

00:47:45.840 --> 00:47:47.199
And it behaves just like it did

00:47:47.199 --> 00:47:49.439
when it was running within Posit Workbench.

00:47:50.959 --> 00:47:52.479
Now I'm going to go through the process

00:47:52.479 --> 00:47:55.439
of showing you how easy it is to share this content

00:47:55.439 --> 00:47:57.280
with everyone here on the line

00:47:57.280 --> 00:47:58.879
once it's hosted on Posit Connect.

00:47:59.520 --> 00:48:01.600
So again, I have control over access.

00:48:01.600 --> 00:48:03.199
I can be very specific.

00:48:03.199 --> 00:48:06.080
I can make it so that I'm the only one that can view it.

00:48:06.080 --> 00:48:07.360
