00:48:54.800 --> 00:48:56.080
with everyone on the line.

00:48:57.840 --> 00:49:00.000
And what's really important here is that you don't,

00:49:00.000 --> 00:49:01.600
as a consumer of this application,

00:49:01.600 --> 00:49:03.439
you don't have to know anything about Shiny,

00:49:03.439 --> 00:49:06.080
version control, Posit Connect, R.

00:49:06.080 --> 00:49:08.399
You can just treat this application as a website.

00:49:08.399 --> 00:49:10.320
So it's really good for getting these insights

00:49:10.320 --> 00:49:12.320
into the hands of people that may not be

00:49:12.320 --> 00:49:13.679
an R developer, for example.

00:49:15.120 --> 00:49:17.280
Now, the only other thing I'll mention here

00:49:17.280 --> 00:49:18.959
as it pertains to version control.

00:49:18.959 --> 00:49:22.399
So as you recall, this application is being deployed

00:49:22.399 --> 00:49:24.560
