00:49:25.360 --> 00:49:28.959
If I come in and I make a change to this Shiny application

00:49:28.959 --> 00:49:30.800
and push it to GitHub repository,

00:49:31.360 --> 00:49:34.159
Posit Connect can automatically detect that change

00:49:34.159 --> 00:49:36.159
and rebuild the content for you.

00:49:36.159 --> 00:49:37.120
All right, so you don't have to worry

00:49:37.120 --> 00:49:38.719
about constantly redeploying it

00:49:38.719 --> 00:49:41.280
every time you make a change to the Shiny application.

00:49:41.280 --> 00:49:43.280
Posit Connect can automatically detect

00:49:43.280 --> 00:49:45.760
if there's been a change to that GitHub repository

00:49:45.760 --> 00:49:48.239
and rebuild it, which can be a really nice feature,

00:49:48.239 --> 00:49:50.399
kind of this continuous integration

00:49:50.399 --> 00:49:51.520
and continuous deployment.

